text: I had the pleasure of hanging-out with Jeremy Renner in a casual setting. He's a very warm, very down-to-Earth kind of guy, and a surprisingly talented pianist, singer, and veritable stand-up comedian. We had an amazing discussion about his career, and  about life in general. He said it has been an honor and a privilege having a role‚Äîespecially how relatable‚Äîso many fans adore, and it's not lost on him how important  it is for them. But remember...despite that fact...he's still just an actor. He gets paid for his portrayals. And while he's thankful and respectful of his fans and the source material that inspires them, when it's all said and done, he's a career professional like anyone else trying to earn a decent living. Credit his his talent that brings the fans that pays the bills. So here's a word of advice: If you're ever fortunate in meeting Mr. Renner, think about how many times people don't show enough common decency not to shout at him by the name of a comic book character, particularly while he's being an ordinary citizen in public, and na√Øvely expect he would be as excited as they are when they do. So try not being quite as obnoxious about it, okay? No matter how much you think he should pay his dues as a celebrity. And if you can get over that, you'll find he's a very cool guy who also happens to be super-famous. P.S.: Thankfully, I didn't end-up finding this out the hard way.

Movie felt like something new and original, although there are familiar tropes but it is all about adventurous spirit and this one has a plenty.
